      "score": 37,
      "comments": 18,
      "author": "noncrab",
      "published": "2026-07-05T08:24:06Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Use native HTML <button> elements instead of styling <div> or <a> tags to inherit default keyboard and screen-reader accessibility features.",
        "Prevent duplicate API calls and race conditions by disabling buttons or showing spinners during pending asynchronous operations.",
        "Ensure interactive elements support both Space and Enter key triggers, preserving expected browser behavior without custom JavaScript workarounds."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Bad Epoll (CVE-2026-46242)",
      "url": "https://github.com/J-jaeyoung/bad-epoll",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/drf6my",
      "score": 47,
      "comments": 12,
      "author": "dzwdz",
      "published": "2026-07-04T18:40:12Z",
      "bullets": [
        "CVE-2026-46242 targets the Linux kernel's epoll subsystem, which manages high-performance asynchronous I/O multiplexing across modern enterprise workloads.",
        "Vulnerabilities in epoll typically enable local privilege escalation, container escapes, or denial-of-service via race conditions or use-after-free flaws.",
        "Administrators should prioritize upcoming Linux kernel patches and restrict unprivileged user namespaces to mitigate potential exploitation vectors."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "I Don't Maintain My Homelab",
